# ls-foundry — core context

Monorepo: **pnpm** workspaces + **Turborepo**. Repo: [github.com/jeffgo10/ls-foundry](https://github.com/jeffgo10/ls-foundry).

## Layout

```
apps/docs/          # Next.js showcase (@ls-foundry/docs) — /stickpak, /3d-label
docs/stickpak/      # StickPak Phase 1 docs (mirror Obsidian StickPak/)
docs/three-d-label-customizer/  # Standalone 3D label warper (mirror Obsidian LS Foundry/)
packages/           # publishable + internal packages
```

## Package scopes

| Scope | Use | Examples |
|-------|-----|----------|
| `@jeffgo10/*` | **Published** to GitHub Packages (`npm.pkg.github.com`) | `shared-types`, `react-canvas-designer`, `canvas-upscaler`, `three-d-label-customizer`, `helpers`, `gl-viewer` (v0.3.1; consumed by **LiteShadeMedia**) |
| `@ls-foundry/*` | **Private** monorepo-only | `docs`, `tsconfig`, `ui`, `utils`, `maps` |

Publish scope must match GitHub owner (`@jeffgo10`). Bump versions in `packages/*/package.json` before `pnpm run deploy`.

## Version bumps (agents)

When you change a published `@jeffgo10/*` package, **bump its `package.json` version in the same work** — do not wait for the user to ask.

| Change | Bump | Example |
|--------|------|---------|
| Bug fix, no public API change | patch | 0.2.0 → 0.2.1 |
| New prop, method, or export (backward compatible) | minor | 0.1.3 → 0.2.0 |
| Breaking layout JSON, types, or consumer API | major | 0.2.0 → 1.0.0 |

Also update the pin table below, `docs/stickpak/phase-1.md` version table + install pins, and any `workspace:*` dependency pins when the upstream API changed (`shared-types` first).

